# SciGate Conventions

## Imports
- All Claude calls through `scigate.utils.claude_client.ask_claude()`
- All repo scanning through `scigate.utils.repo_scanner.scan_repo()`
- Never import `anthropic` directly in agent files

## Agent Pattern
- Each agent function returns a typed dataclass (AuditReport, FixPlan, OrgMemory)
- Findings always use `Finding(check_id=..., title=..., severity=..., description=...)`
- Check IDs: prefix with domain (ML-, BIO-, CLI-, STAT-, DEP-, PATH-, DOC-, ENV-)

## Scoring
- Deductions by severity: CRITICAL=20, HIGH=12, MEDIUM=6, LOW=2
- Field multipliers in `FIELD_MULTIPLIERS` dict in `scoring/engine.py`
- Score range: 0-100, clamped

## Error Handling
- Claude failures should return a graceful default (GENERAL_SCIENCE, empty plan)
- File read errors use `errors="replace"` — never crash on encoding issues
